41#define __BYTE_ORDER _BYTE_ORDER
42#define __LITTLE_ENDIAN _LITTLE_ENDIAN
43#define __BIG_ENDIAN _BIG_ENDIAN
44static inline unsigned short bswap_16(unsigned short v)
45{
46 return ((v & 0xff) << 8) | (v >> 8);
47}
48
49static inline unsigned int bswap_32(unsigned int v)
50{
51 return ((v & 0xff) << 24) | ((v & 0xff00) << 8) |
52 ((v & 0xff0000) >> 8) | (v >> 24);
53}
54#endif /* __APPLE__ */

143static inline unsigned int wpa_swap_32(unsigned int v)

153#define le_to_host32(n) (n)
154#define host_to_le32(n) (n)
155#define be_to_host32(n) wpa_swap_32(n)
156#define host_to_be32(n) wpa_swap_32(n)
157#define host_to_le64(n) (n)

166#ifndef __BYTE_ORDER
167#ifndef __LITTLE_ENDIAN
168#ifndef __BIG_ENDIAN
169#define __LITTLE_ENDIAN 1234
170#define __BIG_ENDIAN 4321
171#if defined(sparc)

174#endif /* __BIG_ENDIAN */
175#endif /* __LITTLE_ENDIAN */

178#if __BYTE_ORDER == __LITTLE_ENDIAN
179#define le_to_host16(n) ((__force u16) (le16) (n))
180#define host_to_le16(n) ((__force le16) (u16) (n))
181#define be_to_host16(n) bswap_16((__force u16) (be16) (n))
182#define host_to_be16(n) ((__force be16) bswap_16((n)))
183#define le_to_host32(n) ((__force u32) (le32) (n))
184#define host_to_le32(n) ((__force le32) (u32) (n))
185#define be_to_host32(n) bswap_32((__force u32) (be32) (n))
186#define host_to_be32(n) ((__force be32) bswap_32((n)))
187#define le_to_host64(n) ((__force u64) (le64) (n))
188#define host_to_le64(n) ((__force le64) (u64) (n))
189#define be_to_host64(n) bswap_64((__force u64) (be64) (n))
190#define host_to_be64(n) ((__force be64) bswap_64((n)))
191#elif __BYTE_ORDER == __BIG_ENDIAN
192#define le_to_host16(n) bswap_16(n)
193#define host_to_le16(n) bswap_16(n)
194#define be_to_host16(n) (n)
195#define host_to_be16(n) (n)
196#define le_to_host32(n) bswap_32(n)
197#define host_to_le32(n) bswap_32(n)
198#define be_to_host32(n) (n)
199#define host_to_be32(n) (n)
200#define le_to_host64(n) bswap_64(n)
201#define host_to_le64(n) bswap_64(n)
202#define be_to_host64(n) (n)
203#define host_to_be64(n) (n)
204#ifndef WORDS_BIGENDIAN
205#define WORDS_BIGENDIAN
206#endif
207#else
208#error Could not determine CPU byte order
209#endif

211#define WPA_BYTE_SWAP_DEFINED
212#endif /* !WPA_BYTE_SWAP_DEFINED */

215/* Macros for handling unaligned memory accesses */
216
217static inline u16 WPA_GET_BE16(const u8 *a)
218{
219 return (a[0] << 8) | a[1];
220}
221
222static inline void WPA_PUT_BE16(u8 *a, u16 val)
223{
224 a[0] = val >> 8;
225 a[1] = val & 0xff;
226}
227
228static inline u16 WPA_GET_LE16(const u8 *a)
229{
230 return (a[1] << 8) | a[0];
231}
232
233static inline void WPA_PUT_LE16(u8 *a, u16 val)
234{
235 a[1] = val >> 8;
236 a[0] = val & 0xff;
237}
238
239static inline u32 WPA_GET_BE24(const u8 *a)
240{
241 return (a[0] << 16) | (a[1] << 8) | a[2];
242}
243
244static inline void WPA_PUT_BE24(u8 *a, u32 val)
245{
246 a[0] = (val >> 16) & 0xff;
247 a[1] = (val >> 8) & 0xff;
248 a[2] = val & 0xff;
249}
250
251static inline u32 WPA_GET_BE32(const u8 *a)
252{
253 return ((u32) a[0] << 24) | (a[1] << 16) | (a[2] << 8) | a[3];
254}
255
256static inline void WPA_PUT_BE32(u8 *a, u32 val)
257{
258 a[0] = (val >> 24) & 0xff;
259 a[1] = (val >> 16) & 0xff;
260 a[2] = (val >> 8) & 0xff;
261 a[3] = val & 0xff;
262}
263
264static inline u32 WPA_GET_LE32(const u8 *a)
265{
266 return ((u32) a[3] << 24) | (a[2] << 16) | (a[1] << 8) | a[0];
267}
268
269static inline void WPA_PUT_LE32(u8 *a, u32 val)
270{
271 a[3] = (val >> 24) & 0xff;
272 a[2] = (val >> 16) & 0xff;
273 a[1] = (val >> 8) & 0xff;
274 a[0] = val & 0xff;
275}
276
277static inline u64 WPA_GET_BE64(const u8 *a)
278{
279 return (((u64) a[0]) << 56) | (((u64) a[1]) << 48) |
280 (((u64) a[2]) << 40) | (((u64) a[3]) << 32) |
281 (((u64) a[4]) << 24) | (((u64) a[5]) << 16) |
282 (((u64) a[6]) << 8) | ((u64) a[7]);
283}
284
285static inline void WPA_PUT_BE64(u8 *a, u64 val)
286{
287 a[0] = val >> 56;
288 a[1] = val >> 48;
289 a[2] = val >> 40;
290 a[3] = val >> 32;
291 a[4] = val >> 24;
292 a[5] = val >> 16;
293 a[6] = val >> 8;
294 a[7] = val & 0xff;
295}
296
297static inline u64 WPA_GET_LE64(const u8 *a)
298{
299 return (((u64) a[7]) << 56) | (((u64) a[6]) << 48) |
300 (((u64) a[5]) << 40) | (((u64) a[4]) << 32) |
301 (((u64) a[3]) << 24) | (((u64) a[2]) << 16) |
302 (((u64) a[1]) << 8) | ((u64) a[0]);
303}
304
305static inline void WPA_PUT_LE64(u8 *a, u64 val)
306{
307 a[7] = val >> 56;
308 a[6] = val >> 48;
309 a[5] = val >> 40;
310 a[4] = val >> 32;
311 a[3] = val >> 24;
312 a[2] = val >> 16;
313 a[1] = val >> 8;
314 a[0] = val & 0xff;
315}

517static inline int is_zero_ether_addr(const u8 *a)
518{
519 return !(a[0] | a[1] | a[2] | a[3] | a[4] | a[5]);
520}
521
522static inline int is_broadcast_ether_addr(const u8 *a)
523{
524 return (a[0] & a[1] & a[2] & a[3] & a[4] & a[5]) == 0xff;
525}
526
527static inline int is_multicast_ether_addr(const u8 *a)
528{
529 return a[0] & 0x01;
530}

575/*
576 * gcc 4.4 ends up generating strict-aliasing warnings about some very common
577 * networking socket uses that do not really result in a real problem and
578 * cannot be easily avoided with union-based type-punning due to struct
579 * definitions including another struct in system header files. To avoid having
580 * to fully disable strict-aliasing warnings, provide a mechanism to hide the
581 * typecast from aliasing for now. A cleaner solution will hopefully be found
582 * in the future to handle these cases.
583 */
584void * __hide_aliasing_typecast(void *foo);
585#define aliasing_hide_typecast(a,t) (t *) __hide_aliasing_typecast((a))
